Product name: Vintage 1980 Wallace Berrie Helm Peyo Smurf Push Puppet Toy Made in Hong Kong British Patent Great Collectible
Description:
This is a vintage 1980s push puppet Smurf toy. Signed 'made in Hong Kong,' 'Wallace Barrie,' 'TM,' 'Helm,' and 'Peyo.' Overall decent vintage, played-with condition that still works. Some wear of the paint on the Smurf's tail, neck, and a few other places. The glue at the seams and holding the feet to the red stand is also yellowing. The product sticker on the base has wear.
Approximate dimensions: 4 inches tall.
This comes from my personal collection of toys. I got this in the early 1980s when the Smurfs cartoon was on TV. Brainy Smurf was my favorite. I occasionally played with this toy. My sister seemed to like it more than I did and was fascinated that it's a type of puppet. I'm downsizing my collection of a few select items to make room for other things.
The Smurfs is a Belgian comic and television franchise centered on a fictional colony of small blue creatures who live in mushroom-shaped houses in the forest. The Smurfs was first created and introduced as a series of comic characters by the Belgian comics artist Peyo (pen name of Pierre Culliford) in 1958, where they were known as Les Schtroumpfs. There are more than one hundred Smurf characters, and their names are based on adjectives that emphasize their characteristics, such as "Jokey Smurf", who likes to play practical jokes on his fellow Smurfs. "Smurfette" was the first female Smurf to be introduced in the series. The Smurfs wear Phrygian caps, which came to represent freedom during the modern era. Thank you, Wikipedia.
A fantastic collectible. Due to age, this item is recommended for display only. Purchase for yourself or give as a gift.
Sold loose and does not include any original packaging. Ships via USPS 2-Day Priority and includes insurance and tracking.

ღ Organic Avocado Oil is loaded with vitamins A,  D, and E, is great at promoting healing, and has anti-bacterial and anti-inflammatory goodness
ღ  Arrowroot powder is a great odor and wetness absorbent in this formula
ღ Bentonite Clay is amazing at absorbing toxins from the body including bacteria, pesticides and metals, contains magnesium and more than 60 other trace minerals
ღ This formula contains probiotic powder in place of baking soda for those who are sensitive.  
The best advantage to having so many ingredients that fight bacteria is that most of us (myself included) have just assumed that the odor we emit while sweating is our own odor, but in fact it is bacteria excrement (poop) that we often find offensive!
This particular listing is for a 2.75 ounce twist-up container, 
place on skin where you intend to use the deodorant and let your body heat warm the mango butter slightly and swipe a couple times, that's all you need!
Store in a cool, dry area; if left in the sun or a hot car it could melt a bit, just place in the refrigerator to re-set.

Product name: Terraforming Mars Player Mat Overlays WITH Backboards
Description:
*PLEASE LOOK CAREFULLY AT THE PROCESSING TIME FOR THIS ITEM*
There is currently a longer processing time expected due to a recent production issue. 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
THIS LISTING IS FOR OVERLAYS THAT CONNECT TO BACKBOARDS (see photos). Each quantity unit represents one player mat. 
If you are looking for Terraforming Mars player mat overlays with NO backboards, please see this listing:
https://www.etsy.com/listing/474641534
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To help support fellow gamers in need, a portion of all proceeds from boardgameboost.com is donated to the Jack Vasel Memorial Fund. Learn more about this fund at www.jackvasel.org.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*This product requires assembly. Please see link to video in listing below.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Terraforming Mars is an incredible game that's tremendous fun, but has player mats that are made of thin card stock which prevents movement of the player mat during game play and creates the risk of pieces being easily bumped accidentally. 
This product solves these issues by providing a backboard for the player mats and an overlay to hold both the resource cubes and the income track marker cubes in their places. Assembly is quick and easy: simply place the player mat on top of the acrylic backboard, lay the clear acrylic cube overlay on top of the player mat, then snap the entire item together with the included fasteners. That's it! You then have a permanent board that never needs to be assembled again. Because of the backboard, the entire player mat can be picked up and moved during game play with the cubes on it.
The overlay has bins for the resource cubes and tracks with small notches for the income marker cubes, plus as a bonus also has a long slot in which to store a supply of player cubes for marking hexes or cards. Each income track also has a cube slot to the right of the "10" space to indicate "10" when income reaches high levels. This slot is rotated 45 degrees to make it easily discernible from other cubes.
Opinions vary on whether there should a divider wall or not between the Energy and Heat resource bins, so now you can have it whichever way you prefer! The overlay comes with a wall there but is built to break off if you prefer to slide your cubes from one bin to another. See the photos and video for more information!
Because of the tight nature of the artwork for the income tracks on the player mats, there is little to no space for material between each numbered square. As a result the overlay tracks are just slightly out of vertical alignment with the player mat, but if you look at the photos and video you can see that it is barely noticeable and will have no impact on appearance or reading what number the marker cube is resting on. 
Each player board measures 9.17 x 6.81 x .24" (233 x 173 x 6mm). A stack of 5 boards is about 1.18" (30mm) tall. A stack of 5 fits into the game box without having to remove the box insert (with some careful arranging of game bits - see images). 
Assembly is easy and requires no glue, but it is strongly recommended that you watch the video guide to assembly. To view, open a separate browser window and copy and paste the following URL:
https://youtu.be/bBmVnjMclUw
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Looking for a box insert that can accommodate these overlays AND store all the game bits in an extremely organized and convenient manner? Then check out the special BGBoost version of the TM insert at Insert Here! The direct link to the TM product is below but you'll find the entire store is full of incredible insert designs. To view, open a separate browser window and copy and paste the following URL:
http://www.inserthere.me/productdisplay/terraforming-mars-bgboost-version
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FAQ
Q: What is this product made of? Is it strong? 
A: This product is made of 1/8" (3mm) cast acrylic. Cast acrylic is most equatable to the properties of glass: it's generally durable, but brittle and can crack and break if dropped on a hard surface or bent too hard. It can also be scratched with anything abrasive so please handle with care. 
Q: What are these strange protrusions from each piece that look like the letter "B?"
A: That is a feature of any product from Boardgameboost.com to assist you in the removal of the protective adhesive paper that the pieces ship with. Instead of using a fingernail to get an edge of the paper, simply snap off each "B" piece and the paper will come with it. "B" stands for "break off." See the video guide linked above for more explanation.   
Q: Can the boards be taken apart once they are assembled?
A: They technically can be, but it is not recommended. The snap-together design is intended to be assembled only once, and taking the board apart weakens the connections and risks damaging the acrylic. Boardgameboost is not responsible for damage caused in this way. 
Please drop me a note if you have any questions or concerns. Thank you for your interest!
INTERNATIONAL BUYERS: Purchases ship with a tracking number, but please be aware that once the US Postal Service has handed a package off to your country's postal system, the tracking number may no longer function. In addition, any packages that are lost after the US Postal Service confirms transfer to your country's postal system are not the responsibility of this store. Every effort will be made to work with you and your postal system to locate the package, but this store will not be responsible for the shipment of a second package at no cost.
WARNING: this product contains small parts and could pose a choking hazard for small children. Please use with care. 
This is an unlicensed, third-party product compatible with Terraforming Mars. All copyrights and trademarks are the property of their respective owners.

As with all Stellar Sunshine Hoops, this hoop is totally custom made for YOU! That means pick the tubing, diameter, and style (collapsible or standard)!
______________________________________________________
✮✮✮TUBING (weight):✮✮✮ 
3/4" 100PSI PE-Midweight- Best for beginners with average/slender frames, intermediate hoopers, and/or hoopers who want to explore off-the-body tricks. Collapsible at diameters 34"
3/4" 160PSI PE -Heavyweight - Best for beginners with larger frames (Not recommended for off body hooping) Collapsible at diameters 36"
1/2" 125PSI PE -Lightest & thinnest- Best for experienced hoopers, children and/or hoopers who want to focus mainly on off body moves. May be suitable for very petite/slender beginner hoopers. Available in diameters 38" and under only. Collapsible at diameters 32"
*All tubing and connectors are made in the USA!*
✮✮✮DIAMETER (size):✮✮✮
As a general rule of thumb, a beginner's hoop should come to about belly button height or 1-2 inches above your belly button when standing. For beginners, slender hoopers tend to prefer belly button height or below, while curvier hoopers tend prefer a couple inches above. Plus Size hoopers should consider 44"-48"
*Not 100% sure of the size? No problem. Just contact me and after a few simple questions, I will determine the best size hoop for your unique needs*
✮✮✮STYLE:✮✮✮
Standard or Collapsible.. Same great price!
***PLEASE WATCH VIDEO TUTORIAL to learn how to properly collapse a collapsible hoop***
www.youtube.com/watch?v=hdodBsAaSZk
Collapsible hoops are just as sturdy as standard hoops. As long as it is always opened and closed correctly, your collapsible hoop will last you many years! Collapsible hoops also take much less time to ship than standard hoops. Because of all these benefits, I recommend the collapsible style for all applicable hoops. Hoops 40" and larger MUST be made collapsible for shipping purposes. Do not store your hoop in the collapsed position or leave it collapsed in high heat areas, such as a parked car in summer time.
All hoops that can be made collapsible will be made collapsible unless otherwise specified. So if you prefer a standard style hoop, you must let me know in the "note to seller" section upon check out.

Product name: Pilot Kakuno Fountain Pen - Fine Nib / Medium Nib - 10 body colors
Description:
Your first encounter with a fountain pen is important. 
That's why Pilot designed the Kakuno pen, a simple fountain pen that is great for beginners. Thanks to its many features that help ease beginners into the world of fountain pens, kids and adults can experience the joy of writing with these delightful instruments. "Kakuno" means "to write" in Japanese, and that's just what this pen helps you do!
Features include the cute smiley face on the nib that always faces up when writing, ensuring correct nib orientation. The "Soft" color pens have a winking smiley face, while the other colors have a regular smiley face. Indentations in the cap make it easy to grasp when uncapping the pen. 
The cap and body are hexagonal, similar to the classic wooden pencil, so that the pen is comfortable to hold and doesn't roll away. The grip is made in a triangular shape so that fingers naturally sit in the correct position. Novices will soon be on their way to becoming seasoned fountain pen users!
One black ink cartridge is included. 
This pen is compatible with Pilot ink cartridges and converters, as listed under Recommended Refills/Parts.
Photos of a pen without its packaging feature the Medium Nib Light Green pen.

Product name: Orange Blossom Spoon Ring - Adjustable - Handmade by Doctor Gus - Beautiful Antique Inspired Flowery Boho Design Replica in Lead Free Pewter
Description:
You are looking at a wonderful flowery ring just waiting to grace your finger. 
The design is based on the antique Edwardian era silverware pattern called Orange Blossom from 1910. This one is a replica reproduced in recycled lead-free Britannia pewter.
All of my rings are 100% handcrafted in the USA by yours truly, me, Doctor gus! 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
You will receive one ring identical to those pictured.
This spoon ring is easy to adjust from a US size 6 through to about a size 9. And can be worn either as a midi ring or a regular ring! 
Just choose the approximate ring size you'd like when adding it to your cart. These rings are adjustable, but it's best if I send one that's close to the size you need already. I tend to make my rings slightly oversize, that way it's easy for you to make the final prefect adjustment yourself! 
Unlike traditional silver spoon rings, my lead-free Britannia pewter spoon rings are self adjustable. Just gently squeeze or pull them with your fingers to obtain the size you need. This adjustability is great if you're giving them as gifts or you want to wear them as midi rings.
Expect some minor variation since each piece is lovingly handmade and small differences in shape and surface detail cannot be avoided in the process. But rest assured that I am a craftsman who would never send you anything I'm not proud enough to call my own. 
I cast these by hand with the help of fellow artisans in the beautiful Pocono Mountains of Northeastern Pennsylvania. It is based on an antique design and has been reproduced in the finest quality pewter. 
Each ring is solid metal that is both lead free and nickel free. It will not turn your finger green or cause an allergic reaction. 
These are not made from real antique spoons, but I think you'll agree that they look just as good!
Care is the same as with any piece of jewelry. Keep it dry and use a soft polishing cloth occasionally if it needs a bit of an extra shine. It's pretty simple. Pewter stays pretty shiny most of the time. 
Personally, I prefer a bit of an antiqued steampunky look, so I've put a light patina on these rings and then hand polished them to achieve that perfect balance of highlights and shadows. I think you'll agree that the result is fantastic!

HOW TO PUT IT ON?
To put in, with a gentle twist motion, pull gently in opposite directions, moving one end up, and the other down, so hoop will keep its shape, as shown in the photo.
WHAT IS GOLD FILLED?
Gold fill comprises of a thick layer of 14 karat gold bonded to a base metal. It is of much higher quality and gold content than gold plated (50,000 to 100,000 times thicker) and is designed to last as long as solid gold. Gold filled wire is a non tarnish material, can be wet and won't cause an allergic reaction.
It does not flake off, rub off or turn colors, As a matter of fact, anyone who can wear gold can wear gold filled without worries of any allergic reaction to the jewelry.
